edu.stanford.nlp.ling.tokensregex.matcher

Class TrieMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<java.lang.Iterable<K>,V>
      • edu.stanford.nlp.ling.tokensregex.matcher.TrieMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - Type of the key elements Iterable of the trie
    V - The value
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Map<java.lang.Iterable<K>,V>

    public class TrieMap<K,V>
extends java.util.AbstractMap<java.lang.Iterable<K>,V>
    Map that takes an Iterable as key, and maps it to an value. This implementation is not particularly memory efficient, but will have relatively fast lookup times for sequences where there are many possible keys (e.g. sequences over Strings). Can be used for fairly efficient look up of a sequence by prefix.
    Author:
    Angel Chang
